sh king","kjv_def":"Adonibezek.","pos":"proper masculine noun","usage":"Adonibezek(3x)"},"H138":{"id":"H138","lemma":"אֲדֹנִיָּה","translit":"ʼĂdônîyâh","pron":"ad-o-nee-yaw'","derivation":"original (prolonged) אֲדֹנִיָּהוּ ; from H113 (אָדוֹן) and H3050 (יָהּ); lord (i.e. worshipper) of Jah;","strongs_def":"Adonijah, the name of three Israelites","kjv_def":"Adonijah.","pos":"proper masculine noun","usage":"Adonijah(26x)"},"H139":{"id":"H139","lemma":"אֲדֹנִי־צֶדֶק","translit":"ʼĂdônîy-Tsedeq","pron":"ad-o''-nee-tseh'-dek","derivation":"from H113 (אָדוֹן) and H6664 (צֶדֶק); lord of justice;","strongs_def":"Adoni-Tsedek, a Canaanitish king","kjv_def":"Adonizedec.","pos":"proper masculine noun","usage":"Adonizedek(2x)"},"H140":{"id":"H140","lemma":"אֲדֹנִיקָם","translit":"ʼĂdônîyqâm","pron":"ad-o-nee-kawm'","derivation":"from H113 (אָדוֹן) and H6965 (קוּם); lord of rising (i.e. high);","strongs_def":"Adonikam, the name of one or two Israelites","kjv_def":"Adonikam.","pos":"proper masculine noun","usage":"Adonikam(3x)"},"H141":{"id":"H141","lemma":"אֲדֹנִירָם","translit":"ʼĂdônîyrâm","pron":"ad-o-nee-rawm'","derivation":"from H113 (אָדוֹן) and H7311 (רוּם); lord of height;","strongs_def":"Adoniram, an Israelite","kjv_def":"Adoniram."},"H142":{"id":"H142","lemma":"אָדַר","translit":"ʼâdar","pron":"aw-dar'","derivation":"a primitive root;","strongs_def":"to expand, i.e. be great or (figuratively) magnificent","kjv_def":"(become) glorious, honourable.","pos":"verb","usage":"glorious(2x), honourable(1x)"},"H143":{"id":"H143","lemma":"אֲדָר","translit":"ʼĂdâr","pron":"ad-awr'","derivation":"probably of foreign derivation; perhaps meaning fire;","strongs_def":"Adar, the 12th Hebrew month","kjv_def":"Adar.","pos":"proper noun","usage":"Adar(8x)"},"H144":{"id":"H144","lemma":"אֲדָר","translit":"ʼĂdâr","pron":"ad-awr'","derivation":"(Aramaic) corresponding to H143 (אֲדָר)","strongs_def":"{Adar, the 12th Hebrew month}","kjv_def":"Adar.","pos":"proper noun","usage":"Adar(1x)"},"H145":{"id":"H145","lemma":"אֶדֶר","translit":"ʼeder","pron":"eh'-der","derivation":"from H142 (אָדַר);","strongs_def":"amplitude, i.e. (concrete) a mantle; also (figuratively) splendor","kjv_def":"goodly, robe.","pos":"noun","usage":"goodly(1x), robe(1x)"},"H146":{"id":"H146","lemma":"אַדָּר","translit":"ʼAddâr","pron":"ad-dawr'","derivation":"intensive from H142 (אָדַר); ample;","strongs_def":"Addar, a place in Palestine; also an Israelite","kjv_def":"Addar.","pos":"proper masculine noun","usage":"Adar(1x), Addar(1x)"},"H147":{"id":"H147","lemma":"אִדַּר","translit":"ʼiddar","pron":"id-dar'","derivation":"(Aramaic) intensive, from a root corresponding to H142 (אָדַר);","strongs_def":"ample, i.e. a threshing-floor","kjv_def":"threshingfloor.","pos":"feminine noun","usage":"threshing-floors(1x)"},"H148":{"id":"H148","lemma":"אֲדַרְגָּזֵר","translit":"ʼădargâzêr","pron":"ad-ar''-gaw-zare'","derivation":"(Aramaic) from the same as H147 (אִדַּר), and H1505 (גְּזַר);","strongs_def":"a chief diviner, or astrologer","kjv_def":"judge.","pos":"masculine noun"},"H149":{"id":"H149","lemma":"אַדְרַזְדָּא","translit":"ʼadrazdâʼ","pron":"ad-raz-daw'","derivation":"(Aramaic) probably of Persian origin;","strongs_def":"quickly or carefully","kjv_def":"diligently.","pos":"adverb","usage":"diligently(1x)"},"H150":{"id":"H150","lemma":"אֲדַרְכֹּן","translit":"ʼădarkôn","pron":"ad-ar-kone'","derivation":"of Persian origin;","strongs_def":"a daric or Persian coin","kjv_def":"dram.","pos":"masculine noun","usage":"drams(2x)"},"H151":{"id":"H151","lemma":"אֲדֹרָם","translit":"ʼĂdôrâm","pron":"ad-o-rawm'","derivation":"contracted for H141 (אֲדֹנִירָם);","strongs_def":"Adoram (or Adoniram), an Israelite","kjv_def":"Adoram."},"H152":{"id":"H152","lemma":"אֲדְרַמֶּלֶךְ","translit":"ʼĂdrammelek","pron":"ad-ram-meh'-lek","derivation":"from H142 (אָדַר) and H4428 (מֶלֶךְ); splendor of (the) king;","strongs_def":"Adrammelek, the name of an Assyrian idol, also of a son of Sennacherib","kjv_def":"A