":"feminine of H158 (אַהַב) and meaning the same","strongs_def":"{affection (in a good or a bad sense)}","kjv_def":"love.","pos":"feminine noun","usage":"love(40x)"},"H161":{"id":"H161","lemma":"אֹהַד","translit":"ʼÔhad","pron":"o'-had","derivation":"from an unused root meaning to be united; unity;","strongs_def":"Ohad, an Israelite","kjv_def":"Ohad.","pos":"proper masculine noun","usage":"Ohad(2x)"},"H162":{"id":"H162","lemma":"אֲהָהּ","translit":"ʼăhâhh","pron":"a-haw'","derivation":"apparently a primitive word expressing pain exclamatorily;","strongs_def":"Oh!","kjv_def":"ah, alas.","pos":"interjection","usage":"Ah(8x), Alas(6x), O(1x)"},"H163":{"id":"H163","lemma":"אַהֲוָא","translit":"ʼAhăvâʼ","pron":"a-hav-aw'","derivation":"probably of foreign origin;","strongs_def":"Ahava, a river of Babylonia","kjv_def":"Ahava.","pos":"proper locative noun","usage":"Ahava(3x)"},"H164":{"id":"H164","lemma":"אֵהוּד","translit":"ʼÊhûwd","pron":"ay-hood'","derivation":"from the same as H161 (אֹהַד); united;","strongs_def":"Ehud, the name of two or three Israelites","kjv_def":"Ehud.","pos":"proper masculine noun","usage":"Ehud(9x)"},"H165":{"id":"H165","lemma":"אֱהִי","translit":"ʼĕhîy","pron":"e-hee'","derivation":"apparently an orthographical variation for H346 (אַיֵּה);","strongs_def":"where","kjv_def":"I will be (Hosea 13:10,14) (which is often the rendering of the same Hebrew form from H1961 (הָיָה)).","pos":"adverb","usage":"will(3x)"},"H166":{"id":"H166","lemma":"אָהַל","translit":"ʼâhal","pron":"aw-hal'","derivation":"a primitive root;","strongs_def":"to be clear","kjv_def":"shine.","pos":"verb","usage":"shineth(1x)"},"H167":{"id":"H167","lemma":"אָהַל","translit":"ʼâhal","pron":"aw-hal'","derivation":"a denominative from H168 (אֹהֶל);","strongs_def":"to tent","kjv_def":"pitch (remove) a tent.","pos":"verb"},"H168":{"id":"H168","lemma":"אֹהֶל","translit":"ʼôhel","pron":"o'-hel","derivation":"from H166 (אָהַל);","strongs_def":"a tent (as clearly conspicuous from a distance)","kjv_def":"covering, (dwelling) (place), home, tabernacle, tent.","pos":"masculine noun","usage":"dwelling(2x), covering(1x), home(1x)"},"H169":{"id":"H169","lemma":"אֹהֶל","translit":"ʼÔhel","pron":"o'-hel","derivation":"the same as H168 (אֹהֶל);","strongs_def":"Ohel, an Israelite","kjv_def":"Ohel."},"H170":{"id":"H170","lemma":"אׇהֳלָה","translit":"ʼOhŏlâh","pron":"o-hol-aw'","derivation":"in form a feminine of H168 (אֹהֶל), but in fact for אׇהֳלָהּ; from H168 (אֹהֶל); her tent (i.e. idolatrous sanctuary);","strongs_def":"Oholah, a symbolic name for Samaria","kjv_def":"Aholah.","pos":"proper feminine noun","usage":"Aholah(5x)"},"H171":{"id":"H171","lemma":"אׇהֳלִיאָב","translit":"ʼOhŏlîyʼâb","pron":"o''-hol-e-awb'","derivation":"from H168 (אֹהֶל) and H1 (אָב); tent of (his) father;","strongs_def":"Oholiab, an Israelite","kjv_def":"Aholiab.","pos":"proper masculine noun","usage":"Aholiab(5x)"},"H172":{"id":"H172","lemma":"אׇהֳלִיבָה","translit":"ʼOhŏlîybâh","pron":"o''-hol-ee-baw'","derivation":"(similarly with H170 (אׇהֳלָה)) for אׇהֳלִיבָהּ ; from H168 (אֹהֶל); my tent (is) in her;","strongs_def":"Oholibah, a symbolic name for Judah","kjv_def":"Aholibah.","pos":"proper feminine noun","usage":"Aholibah(6x)"},"H173":{"id":"H173","lemma":"אׇהֳלִיבָמָה","translit":"ʼOhŏlîybâmâh","pron":"o''-hol-ee-baw-maw'","derivation":"from H168 (אֹהֶל) and H1116 (בָּמָה); tent of (the) height;","strongs_def":"Oholibamah, a wife of Esau","kjv_def":"Aholibamah.","pos":"proper noun","usage":"Aholibamah(8x)"},"H174":{"id":"H174","lemma":"אֲהָלִים","translit":"ʼăhâlîym","pron":"a-haw-leem'","derivation":"or (feminine) אֲהָלוֹת (only used thus in the plural); of foreign origin;","strongs_def":"aloe wood (i.e. sticks)","kjv_def":"(tree of lign-) aloes.","pos":"masculine noun","usage":"aloes(3x)"},"H175":{"id":"H175","lemma":"אַהֲרוֹן","translit":"ʼAhărôwn","pron":"a-har-one'","derivation":"of uncertain derivation;","strongs_def":"Aharon, the brother of Moses","kjv_def":"Aaron.","pos":"proper masculine noun","usage":"Aaron(345x), Aaronites(2x)"},"H176":{"id":"H176","lemma":"אוֹ","translit":"ʼôw","pron":"o","derivation":"presumed to be the 'constructive' or genitival form of אַו ; short for H185 (אַוָּה);","strongs_def":"desire (and so probably in Proverbs 31:4); hence (by way of alternative) or, also if","kjv_def":"also, and, either, if, at the least, [idiom] nor, or, otherwise, then, whether.","pos":"conjunction","usage":"also(1x), and(2x), either(7x), if(1x), nor(2x), or(236x), Otherwise(1x), should(1x), whether(7x)"},"H177":{"id":"H177","lemma":"אוּאֵל","translit":"ʼÛwʼêl","pron":"oo-ale'","derivation":"from H176 (אוֹ) and H410 (אֵל); wish of God;","strongs_def":"Uel, and Israelite","kjv_def":"Uel."},"H178":{"id":"H178","lemma":"אוֹב","translit":"ʼôwb","pron":"obe","derivation":"from the same as H1 (אָב) (apparently through the idea of prattling a father's name);","strongs_def":"properly, a mumble, i.e. a water skin (from its hollow sound); hence a necromancer (ventriloquist, as from a jar)","kjv_def":"bottle, familiar spirit.","pos":"masculine noun","usage":"bottles(1x)"},"H179":{"id":"H179","lemma":"אוֹבִיל","translit":"ʼôwbîyl","pron":"o-beel'","derivation":"probably from H56 (אָבַל); mournful;","strongs_def":"Obil, an Ishmaelite","kjv_def":"Obil."},"H180":{"id":"H180","lemma":"אוּבָל","translit":"ʼûwbâl","pron":"oo-bawl'","derivation":"or (shortened) אֻבָל ; from H2986 (יָבַל) (in the sense of H2988 (יָבָל));","strongs_def":"a stream","kjv_def":"river.","pos":"masculine noun","usage":"river(3x)"},"H181":{"id":"H181","lemma":"אוּד","translit":"ʼûwd","pron":"ood","derivation":"from an unused root meaning to rake together;","strongs_def":"a poker (for turning or gathering embers)","kjv_def":"(fire-) brand.","pos":"masculine noun","usage":"brand(1x)"},"H182":{"id":"H182","lemma":"אוֹדוֹת","translit":"ʼôwdôwth","pron":"o-doth'","derivation":"or (shortened) אֹדוֹת (only thus in the plural); from the same as H181 (אוּד);","strongs_def":"turnings