ary;","strongs_def":"Ulam, the name of two Israelites","kjv_def":"Ulam."},"H199":{"id":"H199","lemma":"אוּלָם","translit":"ʼûwlâm","pron":"oo-lawm'","derivation":"apparently a variation of H194 (אוּלַי);","strongs_def":"however or on the contrary","kjv_def":"as for, but, howbeit, in very deed, surely, truly, wherefore.","pos":"adverb","usage":"but(8x), surely(2x), howbeit(1x), wherefore(1x), truly(1x)"}}